name: Consumer requests enrollment in CoverAll
description:
As a person who is aware in advance that he is not qualified for QHP through the
  exchange, and has not initialized an application through EA, he can request to
  be enrolled in CoverAll. The HBX admin can then enter their information and
  process their application through the families index page.

elements.name: When we login as Hbx admin with read and write permissions then on family tab we should see link DC Resident Application

steps.name: a Hbx admin with super admin access exists
Hbx Admin logs on to the Hbx Portal
Hbx Admin click Families dropdown
Hbx Admin should see an DC Resident Application link
Hbx Admin clicks on DC Resident Application link
Hbx Admin should see DC Resident Personal Information page
HBX Admin goes to register an user as individual
HBX Admin clicks on continue button
user should see heading labeled personal information
HBX Admin should see a form to enter personal information
Hbx Admin should see text Household Info
Hbx Admin should see text Special Enrollment Period
Hbx Admin click the "Married" in qle carousel
Hbx Admin select a past qle date
Employee should see confirmation and clicks continue
I click on continue button on group selection page during a sep
HBX Admin should see the list of plans
HBX admin should see the Metal Level filter
HBX Admin selects a plan from shopping plan page
HBX Admin should see the summary page of plan selection
HBX Admin clicks on Confirm button on the summary page of plan selection
HBX Admin should see the enrollment receipt page
CONTINUE is clicked by HBX Admin
HBX Admin should see broker assister search box
HBX Admin should see the home page with text coverage selected
Hbx Admin logs out
